<TITLE> Suicide blast outside NATO Afghan base </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KHOST, Afghanistan, Mon Jan 19, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A suicide bomber blew up a car laden with explosives outside a NATO base in Afghanistan's southeastern province of Khost Monday, killing at least one Afghan, residents said. A Reuters reporter saw two helicopters hovering over the base which lies on a key road. Foreign forces had cordoned off the road. Earlier Monday, two police were wounded by a bomb in another part of the province which lies near the border with Pakistan and is part of the main bastion for Taliban guerrillas
